Following are the steps to configure pycharm in windows

1. Download pycharm
2. Download python vesion 3 AS version 2  doesnt support pip freeze. support will expire in 2020
3. select pure python as the language.
4.set the location where python 3 is installed in the interpreter.
5. start coding


Following steps are to configure the python on CMD
1. add path variables of path where python 3 is installed
2. https://datatofish.com/add-python-to-windows-path/

Installing virtual env.
1.python -m venv venv/
